ited for first complete mark had no operating system its only system software was few basic routines for input output ssem from which was developed contrast established mathematical convention machine's storage was arranged with least significant digits left thus one was represented five bits rather than more conventional negative numbers were represented using two's complement most computers still do today that representation value most significant bit denotes sign number positive numbers have zero that position negative numbers one thus range numbers that could be held each 40-bit word was −239 − decimal first programs first realistic program be run on mark was search for mersenne primes early april which ran error free for nine hours on night 16/17 june algorithm was specified by max newman head mathematics department at university manchester program was written by kilburn tootill turing later wrote optimised version program dubbed mersenne express manchester mark continued do useful mathematical work until including investigation riemann hypothesis calculations optics later developments main article manchester computers tootill was temporarily transferred from university manchester ferranti august continue work on ferranti mark 1's design spent four months working with company manchester mark was dismantled scrapped towards end replaced few months later by first ferranti mark world's first commercially available general-purpose computer between average size design team working on mark its predecessor ssem had been about four people during that time patents were taken out based on team's work either by ministry supply by its successor national research development corporation july ibm invited williams united states on all-expenses-paid trip discuss mark 1's design company subsequently licensed several patented ideas developed for machine including williams tube design its own computers most significant design legacy manchester mark was perhaps its incorporation i